**Structuring an HTML Form to Collect Unique Identifiers**

To collect unique identifiers like employee IDs, you'll want to ensure proper formatting and validation. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to structure an HTML form to achieve this:

### HTML Form Structure

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Employee ID Form</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Employee ID Form</h1>
    <form id="employee-id-form">
        <label for="employee-id">Employee ID:</label>
        <input type="text" id="employee-id" name="employee-id" required>
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
    <div id="error-message"></div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS Styling (Optional)

```css
/* styles.css */
